Iavan Pijoos, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A Johannesburg Metro Police Department officer was wounded during a shootout with hijackers in Eldorado Park, south of Johannesburg, on Friday, the JMPD said.&nbsp;Two officers responded to a radio message&nbsp;about a Volkswagen Polo that was hijacked earlier on Friday, Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said.Minnaar said information around the shooting was still vague, but confirmed that one officer&nbsp;had been&nbsp;shot in the hip.&nbsp;The officer, who is in his mid-thirties, was transported to Milpark Hospital.No arrests had been made.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.